<h3 id=3D"idx_types_of_isosceles_triangles">Types of Isosceles Triangles</h=
3>
<p>
There are four types of isosceles triangles: <em>acute</em>, <em>obtuse</em=
>, <em>equilateral</em>, and <em>right</em>.
</p>
<p>
An <em>acute</em> isosceles triangle is an isosceles triangle with a vertex=
 angle less than 90=C2=B0, but not equal to 60=C2=B0.
</p>
<p>
An <em>obtuse</em> isosceles triangle is an isosceles triangle with a verte=
x angle greater than 90=C2=B0.
</p>
<p>
An <em>equilateral</em> triangle is a special case of isosceles triangles. =
Note, in an equilateral triangle, all three interior angles are identical t=
o one another, and all three side lengths are equal to one another.
</p>
<p>
Thus, the vertex angle of an equilateral triangle is equal to 60=C2=B0, as =
are the base angles. Try our <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/equi=
lateral-triangle-calculator/">equilateral triangle calculator</a>.
</p>
<div class=3D"article-thumbnail article-thumbnail-width-50">
<img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.=
com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/equilateral-triangle.png" alt=3D"diagram of =
an equilateral triangle showing the sides, angles, and height" width=3D"128=
0" height=3D"1241" class=3D"alignnone size-full wp-image-10753">
</div>
<p>
A <em>right</em> isosceles triangle is an isosceles triangle with a vertex =
angle equal to 90=C2=B0, and base angles equal to 45=C2=B0. This is also re=
ferred to as a <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/45-45-90-triangle-=
calculator/">45 45 90 special right triangle</a>.
</p>
<div class=3D"article-thumbnail article-thumbnail-width-50">
<img loading=3D"lazy" decoding=3D"async" src=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.=
com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/45-45-90-right-triangle.png" alt=3D"diagram =
of a special right 45 45 90 triangle showing legs a and b, hypotenuse c, 45=
 degree angles, and height h" width=3D"1280" height=3D"1280" class=3D"align=
none size-full wp-image-10752">
</div>
<p>
We have a special <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/right-triangle-=
calculator/">right triangle calculator</a> to calculate this type of triang=
le.
</p>
<h2 id=3D"idx_how_to_calculate_edge_lengths_of_an_isosceles_triangle">How t=
o Calculate Edge Lengths of an Isosceles Triangle</h2>
<p>
Given the <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/triangle-height-calcula=
tor/">height</a>, or altitude, of an isosceles triangle and the length of o=
ne of the sides or the base, it=E2=80=99s possible to calculate the length =
of the other sides.
</p>
<h3 data-toc-exclude=3D"">Find the Base Length</h3>
<p>
Use the following formula derived from the <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalcu=
lator.com/pythagorean-theorem-calculator/">Pythagorean theorem</a> to solve=
 the length of the base side:
</p>
<p>
<span class=3D"formula formula--bg-grey">b =3D 2<span class=3D"square-root"=
 aria-label=3D"Square root of a to the 2 power minus h to the 2 power">a=C2=
=B2 =E2=80=93 h=C2=B2</span></span>
</p>
<p>
The base length <em>b</em> is equal to 2 times the square root of quantity =
leg <em>a</em> squared minus the height <em>h</em> squared.
</p>
<h3 data-toc-exclude=3D"">Find the Leg Length</h3>
<p>
Use the following formula also derived from the Pythagorean theorem to solv=
e the length of side <em>a</em>:
</p>
<p>
<span class=3D"formula formula--bg-grey">a =3D <span class=3D"square-root" =
aria-label=3D"Square root of h to the 2 power plus (b divided by 2) to the =
2 power">h=C2=B2 + (b =C3=B7 2)=C2=B2</span></span>
</p>
<p>
The side length <em>a</em> is equal to the square root of the quantity heig=
ht <em>h</em> squared plus one-half of base <em>b</em> squared.
</p>
<h2 id=3D"idx_how_to_calculate_the_angles_of_an_isosceles_triangle">How to =
Calculate the Angles of an Isosceles Triangle</h2>
<p>
Given any angle in an isosceles triangle, it is possible to solve the other=
 angles.
</p>
<h3 data-toc-exclude=3D"">Find the Base Angle</h3>
<p>
Use the following formula to solve either of the base angles:
</p>
<p>
<span class=3D"formula formula--bg-grey">=CE=B1 =3D <span class=3D"fraction=
" aria-label=3D"fraction with 180 degrees minus beta  over 2"><span class=
=3D"num">180=C2=B0 =E2=80=93 =CE=B2</span><span class=3D"visually-hidden"> =
/ </span><span class=3D"den">2</span></span></span>
</p>
<p>
The base angle <em>=CE=B1</em> is equal to quantity 180=C2=B0 minus vertex =
angle <em>=CE=B2</em>, divided by 2.
</p>
<h3 data-toc-exclude=3D"">Find the Vertex Angle</h3>
<p>
Use the following formula to solve the vertex angle:
</p>
<p>
<span class=3D"formula formula--bg-grey">=CE=B2 =3D 180=C2=B0 =E2=80=93 2=
=CE=B1</span>
</p>
<p>
The vertex angle <em>=CE=B2</em> is equal to 180=C2=B0 minus 2 times the ba=
se angle <em>=CE=B1</em>.
</p>
<h2 id=3D"idx_how_to_calculate_area_and_perimeter">How to Calculate Area an=
d Perimeter</h2>
<p>
Given the side lengths of an isosceles triangle, it is possible to solve th=
e perimeter and area using a few simple formulas.
</p>
<h3 data-toc-exclude=3D"">Find the Perimeter</h3>
<p>
You can find the <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/triangle-perimet=
er-calculator/">perimeter</a> of an isosceles triangle using the following =
formula:
</p>
<p>
<span class=3D"formula formula--bg-grey">p =3D 2a + b</span>
</p>
<p>
Thus, the perimeter <em>p</em> is equal to 2 times side <em>a</em> plus bas=
e <em>b</em>.
</p>
<h3 data-toc-exclude=3D"">Find the Semiperimeter</h3>
<p>
Given the perimeter, you can find the semiperimeter. The semiperimeter <em>=
s</em> is equal to half the perimeter.
</p>
<p>
<span class=3D"formula formula--bg-grey">s =3D <span class=3D"fraction" ari=
a-label=3D"fraction with p over 2"><span class=3D"num">p</span><span class=
=3D"visually-hidden"> / </span><span class=3D"den">2</span></span></span>
</p>
<h3 data-toc-exclude=3D"">Find the Area</h3>
<p>
You can find the <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/triangle-area-ca=
lculator/">area</a> of an isosceles triangle using the formula:
</p>
<p>
<span class=3D"formula formula--bg-grey">A =3D <span class=3D"square-root" =
aria-label=3D"Square root of s(s minus a)(s minus a)(s minus b)">s(s =E2=80=
=93 a)(s =E2=80=93 a)(s =E2=80=93 b)</span></span>
</p>
<p>
The area <em>A</em> is equal to the square root of the semiperimeter <em>s<=
/em> times semiperimeter <em>s</em> minus side <em>a</em> times semiperimet=
er <em>s</em> minus <em>a</em> times semiperimeter <em>s</em> minus base <e=
m>b</em>.
</p>
<p>
This is known as <a href=3D"https://www.inchcalculator.com/herons-formula-c=
alculator/">Heron=E2=80=99s formula</a>.</p>
